This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image super-resolution using GANs. The use of multiple feature discriminators also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The mention of morphological components and color discrimination suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Graphics (cs.GR) categories.
